19using std::string;
20
21Atom::Atom(std::string symbol, const uint16_t z, const uint16_t a, const double abundance, const double mass,
22 const double density)
23 : symbol(std::move(symbol)), z_number(z), a_number(a), abundance(abundance), mass(mass), mass_density(density),
24 number_density(density * N_A * 1.e-24 / mass), // Convert from cm^-3 to Angstroms^-3
25 neutron(getNeutronNoExceptions(z, a))
26{}
27
28Atom::Atom(const Atom &other)
29 : symbol(other.symbol), z_number(other.z_number), a_number(other.a_number), abundance(other.abundance),
30 mass(other.mass), mass_density(other.mass_density), number_density(other.number_density),
31 neutron(getNeutronNoExceptions(other.neutron)) {}
32
33Atom::Atom(const NeutronAtom &neutron)
34 : symbol("user"), z_number(neutron.z_number), a_number(neutron.a_number), abundance(0), mass(0.), mass_density(0.),
35 number_density(0.), neutron(getNeutronNoExceptions(neutron)) {}

3120bool AtomEqualsWithNaN(const double left, const double right) {
3121 if (left == right)
3122 return true;
3123 if ((std::isnan)(left) && (std::isnan)(right))
3124 return true;
3125 return false;
3126}

3128bool operator==(const Atom &left, const Atom &right) {
3129 if (&left == &right)
3130 return true;
3131
3132 if (left.z_number != right.z_number)
3133 return false;
3134 if (left.a_number != right.a_number)
3135 return false;
3136 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.abundance, right.abundance))
3137 return false;
3138 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.mass, right.mass))
3139 return false;
3140 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.mass_density, right.mass_density))
3141 return false;
3142 if (!AtomEqualsWithNaN(left.number_density, right.number_density))
3143 return false;
3144 if (left.neutron != right.neutron)
3145 return false;
3146
3147 // passes all of the tests
3148 return true;
3149}

3167const Atom &getAtom(const uint16_t z_number, const uint16_t a_number) {
3168
3169 if (z_number > ATOMS.size() || z_number < 1) {
3170 std::stringstream msg;
3171 msg << "Invalid proton number z=" << z_number;
3172 throw std::runtime_error(msg.str());
3173 }
3174
3175 const std::size_t index = z_number - 1;
3176 const auto result = std::lower_bound(ATOMS[index].cbegin(), ATOMS[index].cend(), a_number, compareAtoms);
3177
3178 if (result == ATOMS[index].cend() || result->z_number != z_number || result->a_number != a_number) {
3179 std::stringstream msg;
3180 msg << "Failed to find an atom with z=" << z_number << " and a=" << a_number;
3181 throw std::runtime_error(msg.str());
3182 }
3183
3184 return *result;
3185}
3186
3192const Atom &getAtom(const std::string &symbol, const uint16_t a_number) {
3193 // special cases for aliases
3194 if (symbol == "D")
3195 return H2;
3196 if (symbol == "T")
3197 return H3;
3198
3199 // linear search
3200 for (const auto &atom_vec : ATOMS) {
3201 if (!atom_vec.empty() && symbol == atom_vec[0].symbol) {
3202 const auto result = std::lower_bound(atom_vec.cbegin(), atom_vec.cend(), a_number, compareAtoms);
3203 if (result != atom_vec.cend()) {
3204 return *result;
3205 }
3206 }
3207 }
3208
3209 // fail loudly
3210 std::stringstream msg;
3211 msg << "Failed to find an atom with symbol=" << symbol << " and a=" << a_number;
3212 throw std::runtime_error(msg.str());
3213}
